# QuantCore — Questrade read-only integration
# ============================================
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your token.
# .env is gitignored and will never be committed.
#
# HOW TO GENERATE A READ-ONLY REFRESH TOKEN (do this yourself in your browser):
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Log into Questrade at https://www.questrade.com
# 2. Go to:  My Account  →  Security  →  Connected Apps & Devices
#            (older UI:  Accounts  →  App Hub, or Settings → API Access)
# 3. Click "Add personal app" / "Generate new token"
# 4. *** IMPORTANT: select ONLY the "Read" access level ***
#    Do NOT enable "Write" or "Trade" scope.
#    A read-only token cannot place orders even if code were to try.
# 5. Copy the token that appears (it looks like a UUID).
#    You will not be shown it again — store it here immediately.
# 6. Paste it below.
#
# TOKEN ROTATION (automatic):
#   Questrade refresh tokens are single-use and rotate on every authentication.
#   run_analysis.py automatically writes the new token back here on each run.
#   If the script is interrupted mid-refresh, re-generate a new token in Step 3.
#
# NEVER share this file, commit it, or paste the token in chat.

QUESTRADE_REFRESH_TOKEN=your_read_only_refresh_token_here

# The api_server field is populated automatically on first run — leave blank.
QUESTRADE_API_SERVER=
